@hnshahRegularly use 3 in times of COVID:
* One in portrait mode for Slack & email
* One 4K super wide for all work (writing, notetaking, browsing, coding)
* Center monitor (laptop) for calendar & video conferencing

Without 3, have to be constantly shuffling windows around.

Oh thank fuck they finally added a manual notetaking feature to the covid tracer app so you can make notes of where you've been if there isn't a QR code.

ABOUT TIME

When it comes to comparisons of UKGov and ScotGov response to Covid, when winkling out the evidence bear in mind ScotGov’s dislike of notetaking, their rush to make use of FOI much more difficult and the ongoing supine reverence of much of the Scottish media.

Before COVID-19 , weekends were meant for Netflix & chill but now they are replaced by webinars & notetaking. With everything moving remote, the number of webinars are definitely on the rise . Great to see founders/VCs/PMs/devs share their learnings to the inquisitive crowd :)
